 :tx/rationale "ASSESSMENT RISK: Convergence Thesis Structural Ceiling — Risk 1. F(S) at 0.62 for 13 sessions may not be a verification bottleneck but the equilibrium point of the F(S) formulation itself. The 7-component weighted sum may asymptotically approach a value below 1.0 due to structural interdependencies between components. Specifically: improving V (validation) requires adding tests, which adds spec elements, which increases the denominator for C (coverage) and I (incompleteness). If these components are anti-correlated by construction — V improvement mechanically suppresses C and I — then F(S) has a structural maximum well below 1.0 regardless of verification effort. This would mean the convergence thesis (ADR-FOUNDATION-014) is unfalsifiable in its current form: F(S) → 1.0 may be mathematically impossible given the component formulation. MITIGATION: The verification sprint (Priority 2) empirically tests this. If F(S) doesn't move after 265 INVs are verified, the formulation needs revision. Possible fixes: (1) decouple component denominators, (2) use relative improvement rather than absolute scores, (3) normalize by phase-appropriate expectations. VERIFICATION: After verification sprint, if F(S) > 0.72 → risk mitigated (formulation works). If F(S) remains 0.60-0.65 → risk confirmed (structural ceiling). INTERACTS WITH: F(S) stagnation diagnosis, verification sprint proposal, saw-tooth validation. TRACES TO: ADR-FOUNDATION-014, ADR-FOUNDATION-020."
